&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Serif Biomedicines is a privately held, early-stage biotechnology company pioneering Modified DNA as a new class of medicines. Modified DNA brings together the best features of mRNA and gene therapy, while mitigating their limitations, by enabling medicines that are durable, redosable, programmable, and scalable. &amp;nbsp;Serif was founded by Flagship Pioneering, an innovation enterprise that conceives, creates, resources, and grows first-in-category life sciences companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flagship Pioneering has created over 100 groundbreaking companies over the past twenty years, all of which are pioneering novel and proprietary biological, industrial, and engineering approaches to solve major needs in human health and sustainability. These companies include Moderna (MRNA), Generate Biomedicines (GENB), Seres Therapeutics (MCRB), Tessera Therapeutics, &amp;nbsp;and Lila Sciences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated Associate Scientist of Immunology to join our therapeutic discovery team. The candidate will focus on hands-on benchwork using &lt;em&gt;in vitro&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;ex vivo&lt;/em&gt; experimental approaches. The candidate must be independent, goal oriented, technically competent and able to efficiently work across multiple projects. We are searching for enthusiastic, innovative, and highly motivated individuals, with scientific background in immunology, cancer immunotherapy, and/or autoimmune diseases, who are comfortable working in a fast-paced entrepreneurial environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently design and execute in vitro assays to evaluate immune cell function, including multi-color flow cytometry, cytotoxicity assays and other functional readouts under the guidance of scientists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ex vivo analysis of immune cells through tissue processing and downstream assays and analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, execute, and troubleshoot experimental protocols under the guidance of senior members on the team, and maintain accurate and timely electronic laboratory notebook records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and communicate experimental data at team meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS or MS degree in biology, immunology, bioengineering or related discipline with 6+ year of relevant industry experience in immunology and/or immunotherapy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experimental skills, including tissue culture, primary immune cell culture, flow cytometry, immunoassay development, and&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;ex vivo&lt;/em&gt; mouse model and NHP sample processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with non-viral delivery technologies and nucleic acid modalities is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with primary human and/or NHP T cells is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented, self-motivated, and comfortable working with highly technical projects and personnel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly adaptable and responsive to delivering challenging commitments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flagship Pioneering and our ecosystem companies are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Flagship, we recognize there is no perfect candidate. If you have some of the experience listed above but not all, please apply anyway. Experience comes in many forms, skills are transferable, and passion goes a long way. We are dedicated to building diverse and inclusive teams and look forward to learning more about your unique background.&lt;/p&gt;
