&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPANY DESCRIPTION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mirai Bio is a privately-held, Flagship-founded biotechnology company that is delivering genetic medicines from promise to performance. Mirai was built to solve one of the field’s central challenges: achieving precise, scalable delivery of diverse nucleic acid payloads to specific cells and tissues, particularly beyond the liver. By combining a large and growing proprietary&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;in vivo&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;biodistribution dataset, machine learning-guided lipid nanoparticle optimization, modular targeted particle design, and integrated translation and manufacturing capabilities, Mirai helps partners accelerate development, reduce technical risk, and pursue high-value programs making delivery a strategic advantage. We are seeking collaborative, relentless problem solvers that share our passion for defining the future of genetic medicines together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mirai Bio is seeking a scientist to advance our lipid nanoparticle (LNP) delivery platform for nucleic acid therapeutics. Mirai Bio is seeking a highly talented and motivated individual to develop and optimize lipid nanoparticle (LNP) formulations. The successful candidate will contribute to both platform innovation and preclinical pipeline programs, working at the interface of formulation science, Chemistry, analytical characterization, and process development.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, formulate, and characterize lipid nanoparticle (LNP) systems for nucleic acid delivery across early research and preclinical development stages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and optimize formulation processes, including microfluidic mixing and scale-up approaches (e.g., TFF, ultrafiltration)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Screen and evaluate novel ionizable lipids and LNP compositions; analyze structure–function relationships to improve delivery performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot formulation and process challenges to enhance robustness, reproducibility, and scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate high-quality, reproducible data and maintain thorough documentation in electronic lab notebooks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare LNP formulations to support internal research and partner programs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with analytical, translational, and Tech development teams to advance platform goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present data and insights clearly to internal teams and contribute to scientific discussions and decision-making&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE &amp;amp; QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ph.D. and 0-1 years or 4+ years (M.Sc.) or 6+ years (B.Sc.) of relevant industry experience in LNP formulation optimizations and drug delivery with strong background in nucleic acid therapeutics and education in life sciences or engineering (Pharmaceutical Sciences, Biomedical Engineering, Biochemistry, etc)
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level (Associate Scientist or Scientist I) will be determined based on experience, technical expertise, and demonstrated impact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience in nanoparticle or LNP formulation and characterization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of drug delivery systems, particularly for nucleic acid therapeutics&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with nanoparticle characterization techniques (e.g., DLS, zeta potential, fluorescence-based assays such as Ribogreen, chromatography)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to design, execute, and troubleshoot experiments independently&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong data analysis, documentation, and communication skills&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&

