&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Apriori Bio, our cutting-edge platform, Octavia™, is a fully-integrated, closed-loop engine functioning as a &#39;Bio-OS&#39; for advanced biotech innovation and biodefense. This biology-enabled AI/ML platform transforms complex biological data into actionable intelligence to map viral fitness landscapes, predict immune escape trajectories, and enable the rapid, modular design of variant-resilient immunological therapies, including vaccines, antibodies, and next-generation immunogens.&amp;nbsp; As the Director of Program Management at Apriori Bio, you&#39;ll be instrumental in driving our mission forward by working closely with senior leaders and engaging with both wet-lab scientists and computational experts. You will coordinate complex initiatives and oversee the preparation of key deliverables, fostering a culture of communication, accountability, and efficiency. By implementing robust project management strategies, you will lead major company initiatives across R&amp;amp;D, operational, and corporate objectives. Your strategic oversight will ensure R&amp;amp;D milestones align with broader corporate strategies, while your exceptional coordination skills will facilitate seamless communication and collaboration between senior leadership and functional teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Director of Program Management to drive coordination and execution across key initiatives spanning R&amp;amp;D and corporate operations. This role will ensure alignment between company goals and day-to-day project execution by managing milestones, tracking cross-functional dependencies, and enabling teams to deliver on critical priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director will work closely with senior leadership to translate strategic objectives into clear operational plans, while helping ensure the organization stays aligned, focused, and moving forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly collaborative and hands-on role for a program leader who thrives in dynamic environments and can bring structure, clarity, and momentum to complex initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
