&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About FL114:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FL114 is an innovative, privately held biotechnology company developing our novel epigenetic editing platform to treat a variety of diseases through precise, tunable modification of gene expression. FL114 was founded by Flagship Pioneering, where companies such as Moderna Therapeutics (NASDAQ: MRNA) and Seres Therapeutics (NASDAQ: MCRB) were conceived and created.&amp;nbsp; With a strong emphasis on innovation and experimental execution, FL114 cultivates a highly dynamic and entrepreneurial environment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FL114, Inc. is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Scientist &lt;/strong&gt;to join our integrated &lt;strong&gt;Platform&lt;/strong&gt; as a key contributor in our &lt;strong&gt;Therapeutics Engineering&lt;/strong&gt; efforts. The successful candidate will be an essential member of a close-knit team of experimental and computational scientists driving FL114’s product generation engine and supporting a broad set of therapeutic programs. We are looking for enthusiastic, detail-oriented, adaptive, and highly motivated individuals with a passion for bringing novel medicines to patients. Applicants should be comfortable working on a fast-paced, cross-functional scientific team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently conduct, optimize and proactively troubleshoot cellular screening assays in a wide range of primary and transformed cell lines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expression and functional characterization of novel biologics modalities using various cell systems and techniques (cell-based assays, RNA/DNA/protein isolation and detection techniques, RT-qPCR, flow cytometry, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive, pilot, and oversee development of a wide range of cutting-edge assays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, procurement, and maintenance of combinatorial libraries for relevant cell-based and cell-free assays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identification and management of external partners (CROs, CMOs, etc).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute routine and advanced molecular biology techniques, including plasmid preparation, RT-qPCR, cloning, RNA/DNA extraction, gel electrophoresis, oligo pool work, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Culture and maintain a wide variety of mammalian cell lines, including transient and stable transfections. Develop cell lines as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and interpret assay data, maintain accurate laboratory notebooks, and communicate results clearly in team meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive optimization and automation of screening protocols, including the use of liquid handling systems and plate readers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing DNA assets for molecular library design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with gene delivery technologies (for example LNP, lentivirus, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to CRISPR-based or other gene editing technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to NGS data sets and its interpretation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with data analysis tools such as GraphPad Prism, Benchling, SnapGene, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptive and detail-oriented with excellent time management and organizations skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional teamwork and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PhD in Cell or Molecular Biology, Biochemistry, or related disciplines with 2+ years of relevant experience in biotech or pharma.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in cellular and molecular biology with hands-on experience in the development and optimization of cell-based assays and library screening assays.&lt;/li&gt;
